{
  "text": "N 0 is the Brunt-Väisälä frequency and h 0 ϭ 2 km/d is the growth rate of the CBL. Q Ͼ 0 during the daytime (t sunrise Ͻ t Ͻ t sunset ), and Q Ͻ 0 during the night (t sunset Ͻ t Ͻ t sunrise ). When A ϭ 0, the duration of the day is equal to the length of the night. We chose A such as to have a daytime of 14 hours and a nighttime of 10 hours, as during a summer day at 54ЊN latitude. During the first day (t sunrise Ͻ t Ͻ t sunset ) the CBL, h D ( x, t), grows monotonically from sunrise to sunset [CITATION_1] :",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "123229984"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "123229984": {
      "title": "Mesoscale energy generated in the boundary layer",
      "abstract": "We examine the kinetic energy that may be generated from surface heating. Cumulonimbus, cumulus, mesoscale and large-scale conversion of potential into kinetic energy can be identified in an idealized way, as distinct processes. Each has a characteristic thermodynamic efficiency."
    }
  }
